        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 3:14PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 312 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a thunderstorm with
torrential rainfall over Asheville, moving south at 5 mph.

Locations to be impacted include...
Asheville, Biltmore Forest, Woodfin, and Enka.

Very heavy rainfall rates up to 3 inches per hour will be possible
in these areas.
</description>
        <instruction>Areas with poor drainage, such as ditches and underpasses may flood.
Avoid these areas and do not cross flooded roads. Water levels of
small streams may also rise rapidly. Seek higher ground if
threatened by flood waters.</instruction>
